   Here's a diagram of a printed page and all the dot commands that
affect it:

|                                     | <- Top margin (MT)
|  Here's our Header!!                | <- Header (HR)
|                                     | <- Blank lines (HM)
|  Text of document                   |
|                                     |
|                                     |
|                                     | <- Blank lines (FM)
|                                     |
|  Here's our footer                  | <- Footer (FO)
|                                     |
|                                     | <- Bottom margin (MB)

   Just keep in mind that most of the time, the default values will
suit you just fine.  There is rarely a need to change items such as
the header and footer margins (HM and FM), which are the number of
lines printed

